The most important thing (in my opinion) that makes a breakfast restaurant good is their willingness to accommodate substitutions.
Any restaurant with a "no substitution" policy is officially off my list.
But fortunately for me, Mike and Ronda's The Place has a very generous substitution policy.
I ordered the Build Your Own Omelet, which comes with meat of your (assuming you eat meat), cheese and veggies of your choice.
My waitress was more than happy to add as many veggies as necessary to compensate for my lack of meat.
And after the omelet, there were hashbrowns and toast.
I swear, the food just wouldn't end!
And the hashbrowns are the really good kind, like you would get at IHOP or Denny's.
That's right, the REALLY good kind!!
The service was great, the food was even better, and the menu has tons of options.
If you're searching for breakfast in the west valley, you're making a huge mistake if you don't opt for The Place.

