Stopped in for breakfast with a friend and to catch up.
I had a breakfast burrito with chorizo with a side of fruit.
The portion was smaller than I expected but I was surprisingly happy about this as I think we are over served at most restaurants and end up with a ton of leftovers.
My burrito was pretty good.
The service was wonderful as my coffee cup was rarely empty, and this was a day I decided to drink A LOT of coffee.
My friend and I had a lot of catching up to do so we were there for an extended time.
I never felt pressured to leave or uncomfortable about staying.
It was a nice experience.
I would definitely return.

